    {
      "label": "Transcript",
      "value": "To the worthy Sons and members of St. Andrew\n\nThe Subscriber begs leave to represent\n\nThat her growing years and infirmities oblige her to beg a continuance of their annual bounty to her this year. By their last she has been enabled to creep thro' twelve months of pain and sickness unable to help herself and a burden to her careful children. She therefore hopes they will not deny it now when it is become even if possible more necessary than before -- In which expectation\n\nShe always is their most humble Servt [servant]\n\nSarah Campbell [signature of applicant]"
